{"title": "Leakage of sensitive data to AppSignal", "summary": " Leaking sensitive data to third-party loggers is a common cause of data leaks and can lead to data breaches. This rule looks for instances of sensitive data sent to AppSignal. ", "description": "\nLeaking sensitive data to third-party loggers is a common cause of data leaks and can lead to data breaches. This rule looks for instances of sensitive data sent to AppSignal.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u2705 When logging errors or events, ensure all sensitive data is removed.\n\n```ruby\nAppsignal.tag_request(user: current_user.email)\n```\n\n\u274c Do not send sensitive data to AppSignal\n\n```ruby\nAppsignal.tag_request(user_id: current_user.id)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-201"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_third_parties_appsignal"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}